Chapter 1. General conditions

Section 1. Objective

This agreement regulates the basic conditions and procedures of the certificate service in accordance with the Electronic Signature Act, its’ ordinance and regulations (hereinafter referred to as “Electronic Signature Act”), and the Certification Practice Statement of Korea Certification Authority Central of Korea Information Security Agency and the Accredited Certification Authority of Koscom (hereinafter referred to as “SignKorea”).

Section 2. Validation and Amendment
① This agreement is valid upon disclosure of the member.
② SignKorea may change the agreement under reasonable conditions, but should immediately give notice of the change. If material changes related to the fees or the rights and obligations of the member, at least a seven day notice will be provided.

Section 3. Disclosure and Rules
① Disclosure of this agreement will be posted at SignKorea’s website (http://www.signkorea.com) or the method specified by Registration Authorities.
② Any issues that are not specified in this agreement will be subject to the Electronic Signature Act and SignKorea’s Certification Practice Statement.


